import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_datetime(data['delay'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce').dt.time
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', label='Median delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'].plot(kind='box')
    plt.axhline(y=data['distance'].median(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend({'Median Distance':data['distance'].median()})
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['origin'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='blue', alpha=0.5, label='Origin')
    data['destination'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color='red', alpha=0.5, label='Destination')
    plt.title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y%m%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data.index)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.axvline(data['date'].min(), color='red', label=f'Minimum Date: {data["date"].min().strftime("%Y-%m-%d")}')
    ax.axvline(data['date'].max(), color='green', label=f'Maximum Date: {data["date"].max().strftime("%Y-%m-%d")}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
